  "prompt": "What are the most advanced car tools that people don't know about yet?",
  "response": "As of 2023, there are several cutting-edge automotive tools and technologies that many people might not be familiar with yet. Here are some of the most advanced car tools:\n\n1. **ADAS Calibration Tools**: Advanced Driver Assistance Systems (ADAS) require precise calibration to function correctly. Specialized tools are now available to calibrate cameras, radar, and lidar sensors, ensuring systems like lane-keeping assists and adaptive cruise control operate optimally.\n\n2. **Digital Inspection Systems**: These systems use high-resolution cameras and software to conduct thorough inspections of vehicles. They can identify issues that might be missed during a manual inspection, such as subtle body damage or wear on components.\n\n3. **Vehicle Diagnostic Everyware**: This refers to cloud-based diagnostic systems that continuously monitor a vehicle's health and performance via the internet. Mechanics can access real-time data to diagnose and fix issues remotely.\n\n4. **3D Printing for Auto Parts**: Advanced 3D printing technology is being used to create custom-made replacement parts, which can be especially useful for rare or vintage cars where parts are hard to come by.\n\n5. **Automated Mechanic Tools**: Robotic systems and automated machines that can perform routine tasks, such as tire changes or fluid level checks, with high precision and speed.\n\n6. **VR Training Systems**: Virtual Reality (VR) training systems are being used to train mechanics on new procedures and technologies. These immersive systems provide hands-on experience without the need for physical vehicles.\n\n7. **Advanced Torque Tools**: Tools equipped with digital torque wrenches that record the torque applied to each bolt, ensuring consistent and accurate tightening across all components.\n\n8. **Smart Diagnostic Platforms**: Platforms that use artificial intelligence to diagnose issues faster by comparing symptoms to vast databases of previous cases and solutions.\n\n9. **Augmented Reality Repair Guides**: AR glasses and apps that overlay digital instructions onto real-world views to guide mechanics through complex repairs step-by-step.\n\n10. **Wireless Lift Systems**: Modern vehicle lifts that use wireless technology to sync and control the lift platforms, allowing for more flexible and safer lifting operations.\n\nThese tools represent the forefront of automotive technology and continue to evolve rapidly, making car maintenance, repair, and customization more efficient and sophisticated.",
